nberg/">Events Gutenberg 0.2.8-alpha</a> is out.</p>\n<p>If this is your first time getting your hands on Gutenberg, <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/wordpress-gutenberg-block-editor-checklist/">Prepare yourself for the New WordPress Block Editor</a>.</p>\n<p>This version is compatible with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>The Events Calendar</strong>: Version 4.6.23 or higher</li>\n<li><strong>Gutenberg</strong>: Version 3.8.0</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See all of the changes included in this release below:</p>\n<h3>Events Gutenberg 0.2.8-alpha</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> &#8211; Add Tickets inside of the plugins/ directory</li>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> &#8211; Add Events Pro inside of the plugins/ directory</li>\n<li><strong>Feature</strong> &#8211; Each block now loads their CSS and JavaScript only when it is present in the post</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Smaller internal changes to accommodate Gutenberg 3.8 code</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Properly load the frontend assets for the Blocks</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Accept responses between 200 and 299 HTTP codes as valid responses</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Prevent to set attributes when arrays have the same content</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Resolve problems with Infinite looping around Google Calendar on the Links Block</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Properly load Price block, avoiding breaking on new Events</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Floating block settings button from Gutenberg 3.8 on the correct place</li>\n<li><strong>Fix</strong> &#8211; Migration from Classic Editor no longer duplicates Blocks</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em><strong>Please note</strong> that just as with the Gutenberg plugin, this extension is not for use on production sites. Like Gutenberg, it should only be activated on a test site or local install.</em></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/announcing-events-gutenberg-extension-0-2-8-alpha/">Announcing Events Gutenberg Extension 0.2.8-alpha</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:39:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"Why Writers, Bloggers, and Content Marketers Will Love the New WordPress Block Editor";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://theeventscalendar.com/content-creation-gutenberg-block-editor/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 18 Sep 2018 17:17:02 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Articles";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Block Editor";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Gutenberg";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"https://theeventscalendar.com/?p=1623771";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:663:"<p>The new Gutenberg editing experience for WordPress can뗪 come soon enough for writers, bloggers, and marketers that create content on a regular basis. Later this year, WordPress 5.0 will be arriving with an all-new block editor that takes advantage of the best the modern web has to offer. The project, codename Gutenberg, represents a huge&#8230;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/content-creation-gutenberg-block-editor/">Why Writers, Bloggers, and Content Marketers Will Love the New WordPress Block Editor</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"Jen";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8253:"<p>The new Gutenberg editing experience for WordPress can뗪 come soon enough for writers, bloggers, and marketers that create content on a regular basis.</p>\n<p>Later this year, WordPress 5.0 will be arriving with an <strong>all-new block editor that takes advantage of the best the modern web has to offer</strong>. The project, codename Gutenberg, represents a huge leap forward for WordPress, empowering users단ven those with less technical prowess닶o customize the content, layout, and design of posts and pages.</p>\n<p>Why is everyone so antsy to get their hands on it? Because creating and publishing content with the block editor is much more tailored towards content creators than it is today.</p>\n<p><em>Disclaimer: WordPress 5.0 is still under development, but antsy folks can download the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/gutenberg/">Gutenberg Plugin</a> and start using it today. The block editor hasn뗪 been officially released, so you should proceed with caution. Conveniently, our <a href="https://theeventscalendar.com/gutenberg-block-editor-free-ebook/">free ebook</a> walks you through the install process step-by-step. <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/11/72x72/1f4aa.png" alt="游눩" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></em></p>\n<h2>Less Headache, More Awesome</h2>\n<p>With the new block editor, making your posts and pages look great is a piece of cake.</p>\n<h4>Blocks Keep It Simple</h4>\n<p><strong>The block editor makes it easy to create rich content</strong> in WordPress and you <em>don뗪</em> need HTML or CSS to do it!</p>\n<p>A big focus of the Gutenberg project is creating a true WYSIWYG (랑hat you see is what you get) experience by more closely matching what you see when youre editing your post with the final product visitors to see on your site.</p>\n<p>Since the block editor already acts like a preview, you won뗪 need to flip back and forth between the admin screen and preview screen making little tweaks over and over again.</p>\n<h4>Consistent Formatting Without Code</h4>\n<p>With the classic editor, you had to fit all of your text, images, and styling into a single space. In the block editor, your rich content is separated into blocks so it뗩 easier to play around and find the layout you like. Even better? You can save time by duplicating your favorite layout on other posts and pages.</p>\n<p>Let뗩 say you뗬e got a killer blog post with quotes from several industry experts. You could enter all that content into the old editor and then add the blockquote styling manually, but thanks to the block editor, you have a better option: use the standard Quote block.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1623785" src="http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new.png" alt="Screenshot: Adding a block quote in the Gutenberg block editor" width="2554" height="1396" srcset="https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new.png 2554w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-140x77.png 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-300x164.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-768x420.png 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-665x363.png 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-430x235.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-645x353.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-1068x584.png 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-460x251.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-600x328.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.5-new-500x273.png 500w" sizes="(max-width: 2554px) 100vw, 2554px" /></p>\n<p>With the Quote block, you can select the style from the dropdown, quickly enter your text, and best of all, know exactly where to input the source of your quote.</p>\n<p>Looks pretty good, doesn뗪 it?</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1623786" src="http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success.png" alt="Screenshot: Block Quote frontend" width="2560" height="1384" srcset="https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success.png 2560w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-140x76.png 140w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-300x162.png 300w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-768x415.png 768w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-665x360.png 665w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-430x232.png 430w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-645x349.png 645w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-1068x577.png 1068w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-460x249.png 460w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-600x324.png 600w, https://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/1.6_quote_block_success-500x270.png 500w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" /></p>\n<h4>Copy/Paste From Anywhere</h4>\n<p>If you use external writing apps like Google Docs, Microsoft Word, or Evernote and try to copy and paste the content into the classic editor, it creates a bit of a mess닥asic text formatting disappears and weird, unexpected bits of HTML show up in the text editor.</p>\n<p>Thanks to Gutenberg뗩 extensive support for copying and pasting content, you can kiss most of those old formatting headaches goodbye. Now, when you move stuff into blocks from your favorite writing tool, the formatting stays intact. Gutenberg also has nifty keyboard shortcuts built in to provide a smooth experience composing content directly in the block editor.</p>\n<h4>Page Building FTW</h4>\n<p>Whether youre writing simple blog posts or packing every page with complex content, the new editor is simply more fun to work in.</p>\n<p>Creating content in the old editor, with its text boxes and form elements, felt a lot like data entry닷tility took priority over aesthetics and user experience. The block editor balances all three extremely well, so instead of data entry, it뗩 much closer to the experience of <strong>page building</strong>. You get the utility of simple form elements when needed, but get to drag and drop the elements on the page.</p>\n<p>Because there뗩 visual parity between what you see while youre creating and what renders on the front end when you publish, you have much more flexibility to play with your page layout and interject things like CTA buttons, embeds, and more.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1623821" src="http://theeventscalendar.com/content/uploads/2018/09/blockeditordemo.gif" alt="GIF: block editor demo" width="600" height="338" /></p>\n<p>Gutenberg helps us easily create user-friendly layouts for posts and pages, which translates into higher page views and increased conversions. When your content is easy to read at a glance, people are more likely to share it with others <em>and</em> spend more time reading other posts and pages on your site. Who doesn뗪 want that?</p>\n<h2>Get Your Hands on Gutenberg Now</h2>\n<p>We뗬e got good news닻ou can experience the new block editor right now using the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/gutenberg/">WordPress Gutenberg plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>And it gets even better&#8230;our free ebook covers all things WordPress 5.0 and the new Gutenberg block editor, including step-by-step instructions to prepare your site.</p>\n<p><a class="btn-red" href="#https://theeventscalendar.com/gutenberg-block-editor-free-ebook/">Download the free ebook</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/content-creation-gutenberg-block-editor/">Why Writers, Bloggers, and Content Marketers Will Love the New WordPress Block Editor</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"href";s:35:"https://theeventscalendar.com/feed/";s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:"type";i:128;s:7:"headers";O:42:"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary":1:{s:7:"\0*\0data";a:10:{s:4:"date";s:29:"Fri, 19 Oct 2018 14:20:20 GMT";s:12:"content-type";s:34:"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-